<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-43285AC7-EDFF-42E6-A29B-7033DEEA1291" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-43285AC7-EDFF-42E6-A29B-7033DEEA1291" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to send (failing) parts back to CPP and apply for a warranty</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-F04DCD9F-F5C4-4499-B723-A3B035AE0D80"><p class="- topic/p "> Entering information in ADAM is required to apply for a warranty 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-5D4B711C-CB47-4EB3-A5B3-7446523274EF" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><p class="- topic/p "> Applying a warranty on all failing parts requires proper administration in ADAM. 
</p><table id="GUID-3F848A13-A7AF-4FF2-A3AA-28F2765E7885" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="5.47*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Check on warranty</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For the most expensive parts (printhead, chiller, UV lamps, and printer) warranty can be checked in PRISMAservice, see the link Warranty and contract screen in PRISMAservice. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Collect</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Enter a new reason, e.g. "PH" 
</p><fig id="GUID-4E689460-31D8-4BE0-B027-D89FF2080C29" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-EE6641D7-4424-4CB0-BBBE-19CCC2EF35B1-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EE6641D7-4424-4CB0-BBBE-19CCC2EF35B1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Repair &amp; Evaluate</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Enter the reason for removal. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In the case of printheads: indicate the PH: M3, Y4, K5, or C6 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Add the reason for removal of the part: EC (for error code) xxx, PQ banding, noise, smell, etc. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Press on "Done". 
</p><fig id="GUID-108BCC55-5A35-42A5-9815-A95D87D251D0" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-CA2193BD-9F9E-4522-B948-EE2E9A872108-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CA2193BD-9F9E-4522-B948-EE2E9A872108-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-43E07556-7A11-48A1-B631-DAB6947EC4D8" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-A342278E-6B4E-4C66-BB4C-F13240FD428E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A342278E-6B4E-4C66-BB4C-F13240FD428E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Press on "Add parts". 
</p><fig id="GUID-669BBE50-8CEA-414A-BDDE-B522C3F9903E" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-9F039493-DC8C-4DF7-8F06-405B69C13355-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9F039493-DC8C-4DF7-8F06-405B69C13355-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-F3B6D3A5-2B49-4EEB-9CDC-B44280679F52" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-900AA95C-6A15-4C51-9933-67D9F4FD5F1D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-900AA95C-6A15-4C51-9933-67D9F4FD5F1D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Press "Add Part" and add the replaced part. 
</p><fig id="GUID-ED355ACC-9580-43E2-BC65-BF989D5C6B24" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-155F701A-723A-4EED-8ABC-C8AA9084E794-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-155F701A-723A-4EED-8ABC-C8AA9084E794-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Exit</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Press on 'Exit with save'. 
</p><fig id="GUID-03844309-7220-4AFC-A218-C9E0B9F797AE" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-03E96C72-764C-45C8-B2F8-ADB832EAC3B3-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-03E96C72-764C-45C8-B2F8-ADB832EAC3B3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The most expensive parts (printhead, UV LED Lamp controller, UV lamps) must be returned to CPP. Download the complaint form in PRISMAservice, complete this in Adobe Acrobat Reader and submit this according to the instructions. The remaining parts do not need to be sent back to CPP, these will be compensated in 3 months. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If a part needs to be shipped via UPS, CPP will provide: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">the account number 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> the delivery number – Mandatory to mention on the UPS label! 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The notification number and part number 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">The RSHQ/NSO is responsible for creating the UPS label and planning the pickup/informing the technician of the drop-off. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-45FF6877-55EA-4385-A4B1-00162E8E6581.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>